# (git 8) Analysis VI (Demographic History)

This pipeline can be executed as follows:

```sh
cd $BASE_DIR/nf/08_analysis_msmc
source ../../sh/nextflow_alias.sh
nf_run_msmc
```

## Summary

The demographic history rate is inferred within the [**nextflow**](https://www.nextflow.io/) script `analysis_msmc.nf` (located under `$BASE_DIR/nf/08_analysis_msmc/`), which runs on the _SNPs only_ data set.
Below is an overview of the steps involved in the inference.
(The <span style="color:#4DAF4A">green dot</span> indicates the genotype input, <span style="color:#E41A1C">red arrows</span> depict output that is exported for further use.)

## Details of `analysis_msmc.nf`

### Data preparation

The first part of the scripts includes a large block of preparation work.
In this initial block, the data masks are being generated based on the samples coverage statistics combined with the locations of idels and the reference genomes mappability.

The whole script is opened by a creating a channel for the linkage groups since the coverage statistics are being created on a linkage group basis.

<div class="kclass">

<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode">#<span class="hl opt">!/</span>usr<span class="hl opt">/</span>bin<span class="hl opt">/</span>env nextflow
<span class="hl slc">// git 8.1</span>
<span class="hl slc">// create channel of linkage groups</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">( (</span><span class="hl str">&#39;01&#39;</span>..<span class="hl str">&#39;09&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">) + (</span><span class="hl str">&#39;10&#39;</span>..<span class="hl str">&#39;19&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">) + (</span><span class="hl str">&#39;20&#39;</span>..<span class="hl str">&#39;24&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">) )</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;LG&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">+</span> it <span class="hl opt">}</span>
	.into<span class="hl opt">{</span> lg_ch1<span class="hl opt">;</span> lg_ch2<span class="hl opt">;</span> lg_ch3 <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Then the phased genotype data is opened (for later use in msmc).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.2</span>
<span class="hl slc">// open phased genotype data</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.fromFilePairs<span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;../../1_genotyping/4_phased/phased_mac2.vcf.{gz,gz.tbi}&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> vcf_msmc <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

To extract the sequencing depth for each individual, the unphased genotypes are opened as well (as this information is lost during phasing).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.3</span>
<span class="hl slc">// open unphased genotype data to extract depth information</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.fromFilePairs<span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;../../1_genotyping/3_gatk_filtered/filterd_bi-allelic.vcf.{gz,gz.tbi}&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> vcf_depth <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The outgroups are removed from the data set and the depth is reported for each individual.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.4</span>
<span class="hl slc">// gather depth per individual</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> gather_depth <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_20g2h_split_by_sample&#39;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../metadata&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> vcfID<span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> vcf_depth

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;depth_by_sample.txt&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> depth_ch
	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	vcfsamplenames</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">| \</span>
<span class="hl str">		 grep -v &quot;tor</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">|tab</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">|flo&quot; &gt; pop.txt</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	vcftools \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--gzvcf</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>
<span class="hl str">		--keep pop.txt \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--depth \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--stdout &gt; depth_by_sample.txt</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The depth information is fed into a channel so that the information is accessible for `nextflow`.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.5</span>
<span class="hl slc">// create channel out of sequencing depth table</span>
depth_ch
	.splitCsv<span class="hl opt">(</span>header<span class="hl opt">:</span>true<span class="hl opt">,</span> sep<span class="hl opt">:</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl esc">\t</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> row <span class="hl opt">-&gt; [</span> id<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.INDV<span class="hl opt">,</span> sites<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.N_SITES<span class="hl opt">,</span> depth<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.MEAN_DEPTH<span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{ [</span>it.id<span class="hl opt">,</span> it.sites<span class="hl opt">,</span> it.depth<span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.set <span class="hl opt">{</span> depth_by_sample_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Next, a channel is created from all the original `.bam` files from the mapped sequences ([git 1.6](git-1-genotyping-i-snps-only.html)).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.6</span>
<span class="hl slc">// create channel from bam files and add sample id</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.fromPath<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;../../1_genotyping/0_dedup_bams/*.bam&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span> <span class="hl opt">-&gt;</span>
				def key <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span>.name.toString<span class="hl opt">()</span>.tokenize<span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&#39;.&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>.get<span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
				return tuple<span class="hl opt">(</span>key<span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">)}</span>
				.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> sample_bams <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The previously created depth information is attached to the `bam` channel...


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.7</span>
<span class="hl slc">// combine sample bams and sequencing depth</span>
sample_bams
	.join<span class="hl opt">(</span> depth_by_sample_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> sample_bam_and_depth <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

... and the genotype data and individual linkage groups are added.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.8</span>
<span class="hl slc">// multiply the sample channel by the linkage groups</span>
sample_bam_and_depth
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_msmc <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> lg_ch1 <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> samples_msmc <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Now, the data is split by individual and all the additional information is passed on to the masking (git 8.10) as well as to the production of the the individuals segregating sites (git 8.11).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.9</span>
<span class="hl slc">// split vcf by individual</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> split_vcf_by_individual <span class="hl opt">{</span>

### Grouping of individuals

At this point, the data masks are prepared and the samples can be assigned to their respective groups for their demographic history and and cross-coalescence rate inference.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.12</span>
<span class="hl slc">//  assign samples randomly across MSMC and cross coalescence runs</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> msmc_sample_grouping <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;L_loc_msmc_grouping&quot;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/msmc/setup&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">module</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;R3.5.2&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;msmc_grouping.txt&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> msmc_grouping
	<span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;msmc_cc_grouping.txt&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span>  cc_grouping

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	Rscript --vanilla \$BASE_DIR/R/sample_assignment_msmc.R \</span>
<span class="hl str">			\$BASE_DIR/R/distribute_samples_msmc_and_cc.R \</span>
<span class="hl str">			\$BASE_DIR/R/cross_cc.R \</span>
<span class="hl str">			\$BASE_DIR/metadata/sample_info.txt \</span>
<span class="hl str">			msmc</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The results of the random assignment are being fed into a channel.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.13</span>
<span class="hl slc">// read grouping into a channel</span>
msmc_grouping
	.splitCsv<span class="hl opt">(</span>header<span class="hl opt">:</span>true<span class="hl opt">,</span> sep<span class="hl opt">:</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl esc">\t</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> row <span class="hl opt">-&gt; [</span> run<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.msmc_run<span class="hl opt">,</span> spec<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.spec<span class="hl opt">,</span> geo<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.geo<span class="hl opt">,</span> group_nr<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.group_nr<span class="hl opt">,</span> group_size<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.group_size<span class="hl opt">,</span> samples<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.samples <span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.set <span class="hl opt">{</span> msmc_runs <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Since this script uses an unorthodox way of making the results of the data preparation available to all following processes by exporting them back to the root folder, the following dummy process is installed to wait for the data preparation to finish before proceeding with the workflow.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.14</span>
<span class="hl slc">// wait for bam_caller and generate_segsites to finish:</span>
<span class="hl com">/*this &#39;.collect&#39; is only meant to wait until the channel is done,</span>
<span class="hl com">  files are being redirected via publishDir*/</span>
coverage_by_sample_lg.collect<span class="hl opt">()</span>.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;coverage done!&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">}</span>.into<span class="hl opt">{</span> coverage_done<span class="hl opt">;</span> coverage_cc <span class="hl opt">}</span>
segsites_by_sample_lg.collect<span class="hl opt">()</span>.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;segsites done!&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">}</span>.into<span class="hl opt">{</span> segsites_done<span class="hl opt">;</span> segsites_cc <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

To set up the `msmc2` runs, the sample grouping is waiting for the dummy process to finish.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.15</span>
<span class="hl slc">// attach masks to MSMC group assignment</span>
lg_ch2
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> msmc_runs <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> coverage_done <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> segsites_done <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{[</span>it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">],</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">]</span>.run<span class="hl opt">,</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">]]}</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> msmc_grouping_after_segsites <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Then, the specific `msmc2` input files are compiled from the combined masks of the involved samples (for each linkage group individually).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.16</span>
<span class="hl slc">// generating MSMC input files (4 or 3 inds per species)</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> generate_multihetsep <span class="hl opt">{</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl com">/* content msmc_gr: val( msmc_run ), val( spec ), val( geo ), val( group_nr ), val( group_size ), val( samples ) */</span>
	<span class="hl com">/*[LG20, [msmc_run:45, spec:uni, geo:pan, group_nr:4, group_size:3, samples:ind1, ind2, ind3], coverage done!, segsites done!]*/</span>

<span class="hl str">		sed &quot;s|, |</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">n--mask=\</span><span class="hl ipl">${COVDIR}</span><span class="hl str">|g; s|^|--mask=\</span><span class="hl ipl">${COVDIR}</span><span class="hl str">|g&quot; | \</span>

<span class="hl str">		sed &quot;s|, |</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">n\</span><span class="hl ipl">${SEGDIR}</span><span class="hl str">|g; s|^|\</span><span class="hl ipl">${SEGDIR}</span><span class="hl str">|g&quot; | \</span>

The input files of all linkage group are collected for each sample grouping.


<div class="sourceCode">

And finally `msmc2` is executed to infer the demographic history of the involved samples.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.18</span>
<span class="hl slc">// run msmc</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> msmc_run <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;L_190g100h_msmc_run&quot;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/msmc/output/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">,</span> pattern<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.final.txt&quot;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/msmc/loops/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">,</span> pattern<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.loop.txt&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> msmc_run<span class="hl opt">,</span> lg <span class="hl opt">,</span> spec<span class="hl opt">,</span> geo<span class="hl opt">,</span> group_size<span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> hetsep <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> msmc_input

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;*.msmc2.*.txt&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> msmc_output

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	NHAP=\$(echo \$(seq 0 \$((</span><span class="hl ipl">${group_size[0]}</span><span class="hl str">*2-1))) | sed &#39;s/ /,/g&#39; )</span>
<span class="hl str">	INFILES=\$( echo</span> <span class="hl ipl">${hetsep}</span> <span class="hl str">)</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	msmc2 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-m 0.00254966 -t 8 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-p 1*2+25*1+1*2+1*3 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-o run</span><span class="hl ipl">${msmc_run}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec[0]}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${geo[0]}</span><span class="hl str">.msmc2 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-I \</span><span class="hl ipl">${NHAP}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>
<span class="hl str">		\</span><span class="hl ipl">${INFILES}</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The process cross-coalescence rate is similar (with git 8.19 being the equivalent of git 8.13).
So, again the grouping information in fed into a channel.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.19</span>
<span class="hl slc">// generate MSMC cross coalescence input files (2 inds x 2 species)</span>
cc_grouping
	.splitCsv<span class="hl opt">(</span>header<span class="hl opt">:</span>true<span class="hl opt">,</span> sep<span class="hl opt">:</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl esc">\t</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> row <span class="hl opt">-&gt; [</span> run<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.run_nr<span class="hl opt">,</span> geo<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.geo<span class="hl opt">,</span> spec_1<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.spec_1<span class="hl opt">,</span> spec_2<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.spec_2<span class="hl opt">,</span> contrast_nr<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.contrast_nr<span class="hl opt">,</span> samples_1<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.samples_1<span class="hl opt">,</span> samples_2<span class="hl opt">:</span>row.samples_2 <span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.set <span class="hl opt">{</span> cc_runs <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The groups wait for the data preparation to finish.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.20</span>
<span class="hl slc">// attach masks to cross coalescence group assignment</span>
lg_ch3
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> cc_runs <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> coverage_cc <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> segsites_cc <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{[</span>it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">],</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">]</span>.run<span class="hl opt">,</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">]]}</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> cc_grouping_after_segsites <span class="hl opt">}</span>

The `msmc2` input files are being compiled based on the involved samples (for each linkage group).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">

And  `msmc2` is executed to infer the cross-coalescence rate of the involved samples.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 8.23</span>
<span class="hl slc">// run cross coalescence</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> cc_run <span class="hl opt">{</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/cross_coalescence/output/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">tag</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${cc_run}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${geo[0]}</span><span class="hl str">:</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1[0]}</span><span class="hl str">/</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2[0]}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span>
	conda <span class="hl str">&quot;$HOME/miniconda2/envs/py3&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> cc_run<span class="hl opt">,</span> lg <span class="hl opt">,</span> spec1<span class="hl opt">,</span> spec2<span class="hl opt">,</span> geo<span class="hl opt">,</span> contr_nr<span class="hl opt">,</span> samples_1<span class="hl opt">,</span> samples_2<span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> hetsep <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> cc_input

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;cc_run.*.final.txt.gz&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> cc_output

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	INFILES=\$( echo</span> <span class="hl ipl">${hetsep}</span> <span class="hl str">)</span>
<span class="hl str">	POP1=\$( echo &quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${samples_1}</span><span class="hl str">&quot; | sed &#39;s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">[//g; s/, /,/g; s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">]//g&#39; )</span>

<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	msmc2 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-m 0.00255863 -t 24 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-p 1*2+25*1+1*2+1*3 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-o cc_run.</span><span class="hl ipl">${cc_run}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1[0]}</span><span class="hl str">.msmc \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-I 0,1,2,3 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		\</span><span class="hl ipl">${INFILES}</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	msmc2 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-m 0.00255863 -t 24 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-p 1*2+25*1+1*2+1*3 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-o cc_run.</span><span class="hl ipl">${cc_run}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2[0]}</span><span class="hl str">.msmc \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-I 4,5,6,7 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		\</span><span class="hl ipl">${INFILES}</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	msmc2 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-m 0.00255863 -t 24 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-p 1*2+25*1+1*2+1*3 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-o cc_run.</span><span class="hl ipl">${cc_run}</span><span class="hl str">.cross.msmc \</span>

<span class="hl str">		cc_run.</span><span class="hl ipl">${cc_run}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2[0]}</span><span class="hl str">.msmc.final.txt | \</span>
